Comment: The most luxuriant Academic Festival Overture I've heard, with prominent brass and pronounced cymbals. Too over the top but it is surprises me that it's coming from MTT.
Showcases Ormandy in his prime. Beware the poor sonics.
How muscular and energetic. Jansons in his prime.
It's just… so bad. Solti clearly being too old with the lethargic tempi.

Work: Die Entführung aus dem Serail Overture

Comment: Despite a slow start, the performance is solid. As with Horenstein, the recording sounds 2 decades older than the performance.
Amazing. First interpretation where the last movement did not bore me to tears.
The performance just lacks the passion that this work demands. Jansons is Jansons.
